Preheat the oven to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Halve the @baby potatoes{500%g} lengthways, quartering any larger pieces. Pop onto a lined #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil{to taste} and season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Rub the oil over the potatoes then lay them cut-side down on the baking tray.

Roast on the top shelf of the oven until fork tender, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn the tray halfway through.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, mix together the @honey{2%sachets}, @aioli{1%sachet} and @korma curry paste{1%sachet}.

Trim the @green beans{75%g}.

Trim the @carrot{1} and halve lengthways (no need to peel). Chop into 1cm wide, 5cm long batons.

Halve the @chilli{1} and discard the core and seeds. Finely chop.

Bash the unopened sachet of @peanuts{20%g} with a #pot{} or #rolling pin{}.

Place a pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Once hot, add the green beans and carrots and fry until starting to char, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add a splash of @water{to taste} and cover with a #lid{} or some #foil{}. Cook until tender, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Transfer the veg to a #bowl{}. Toss with @sweet Asian sauce{1%sachet} and half the chopped chilli (use less if you don't like spice).

Season to taste with salt and pepper. Set aside and cover to keep warm.

Beat @egg{1} in a bowl.

> Double the egg for 4p.

In another bowl, season the @breadcrumbs{1%pack} with salt and pepper.

Wipe and return the pan to high heat with 2cm oil.

Season the @diced Irish chicken breast{260%g} with salt and pepper.

Toss the chicken first in egg then breadcrumbs. Ensure it's well coated.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw chicken.

> TIP: Notice a stronger smell from your chicken? Don't worry, this is normal due to packaging used to keep it fresh.

Fry the chicken until golden and cooked through, ~{6-8%minutes}. Turn every 2-3 mins.

Transfer to a #plate{} lined with #kitchen paper{}. 

> IMPORTANT: Chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Place the @bao buns{6} on a plate (three at a time). Microwave covered for ~{1%minute}.

> TIP: Don't have a microwave? Boil 2cm of water in a pot. Pop a colander lined with a baking sheet on top. Place 3 bao at a time on the baking sheet. Cover and steam, 3-4 mins.

Fill each bao with crispy chicken.

Drizzle the katsu curry sauce over the top.

Serve the warm Asian veg and roast potatoes on the side.

Finish with a scattering of crushed peanuts and remaining chopped chilli.